                         Profession Work Orders

    Profession work orders are posted in the profession building, 4e, n
from Center of Town. The board rotates every DarkWind day with requests
for saved materials and crafted items.

Commands:
  workorders
  workorder <#>
  workorder complete <#>

    Work orders may ask for herbs, ores, bars, skins, leathers, reagents,
potions, bags, tailored clothing, bandages, or other profession-crafted
goods. Saved-material orders pull directly from your reagent/material
storage. Crafted-item orders require the item in your inventory and consume
it when completed.

    Rewards include coins, experience, profession practice, and sometimes
bonus shards or recipe cards. Some rare utility recipes, such as masterwork
polish, are available through work orders.

    Profession-crafted gear can also be improved in the profession building:

  inlay <crafted item> with <shard>

    Inlaying consumes one saved shard and adds a small stat or resistance
bonus to a profession-crafted item. Each item can only hold one inlay.
See 'help inlays' for more detail.

Getting started:
  1. Go to the profession building, 4e, n from Center of Town.
  2. Use 'workorders' at the board.
  3. Use 'workorder <#>' to inspect the material or item needed.
  4. Gather, craft, or manufacture the requested turn-in.
  5. Use 'workorder complete <#>' to claim the reward.
